summary: Move of the Week: Push-Up With Alternating Knee Tap
title: Move of the Week: Push-Up With Alternating Knee Tap
body:
Jay Sullivan

Any transfer that solely works one a part of your physique is, frankly, old-fashioned. Out are the single-note workouts, and in are people who interact a number of muscle teams. For anybody with much less time on his or her fingers (isn’t that everybody?), or these with quick exercise-attention spans, this Transfer of the Week, offers double (or triple) the outcomes.

Sculpt your arms, core, and bum with the Push-Up with Alternating Knee Faucet—it’s a mouthful, however with a burn like this, who cares what the title is?

Incorporate this transfer into your regular strength-training routine, do a number of units at high-intensity after a sweaty cardio session, or simply merely use it to combine up a boring at-home exercise.

What to do: Begin in “up” a part of push-up, fingers instantly beneath shoulders, physique straight. Interact core; bend elbows to decrease physique towards flooring. Press again up; carry left knee to outdoors of left elbow; pause for two seconds, then return to beginning place. Do one other push-up, carry proper knee to proper elbow, return to start out; that’s 1 rep. In the event you want a little bit modification to make it simpler, simply carry knees to the ground.

This MOW is principally a combo of conventional push-ups and mountain climbers. Remember to maintain your butt down and again straight while you carry out the push-up. And while you come up right into a plank formation, consider a slowed-down mountain climber with wider knee crunches for the knee-taps.

An alternative choice is to carry your knee throughout the chest (i.e. left knee to proper facet of chest) while you crunch in, so you’re employed your obliques as nicely.

  • Combine-and-Match Whole-Physique Exercise
  • Create Your Personal Sculpting Exercise

title: Red Carpet Recipes
body:
By Frances Largeman-Roth, RD

It’s lastly time for the Oscars! I’m positively a film buff, however for me it’s as a lot in regards to the spectacle of the entire occasion as it’s about who truly wins. This yr I’ll be notably blissful to place up my aching ft whereas watching Sean, Brad, Angelina, Kate, and Meryl stroll the crimson carpet.

I normally host slightly get-together for the awards and go all out with the food and drinks. This yr I plan to be extra cost-conscious whereas nonetheless treating my visitors to some implausible, little-black-dress-appropriate nibbles.

Sips
Kir Royale
That is my all-time favourite stylish, female cocktail.  When occasions are flush, I make it with Champagne, however Cava is the proper various for proper now. The Spanish glowing wine usually runs about $eight a bottle. And as a substitute of blending it with crème de cassis, attempt a shot of antioxidant-packed pomegranate juice. Pour a couple of quarter inch right into a champagne flute, then high it off with the glowing wine. Be certain that all components are chilled earlier than you begin mixing.

Ginger saketini
I’m not such an enormous fan of sake by itself (because of a foul expertise involving tiny fried fish again within the ‘90s), however it’s fairly refreshing when combined right into a cocktail. You may get a 750 ml bottle of sake for $10, and the remainder of the components—ginger ale, contemporary ginger, lemons—are all fairly low-cost. Skip the crystallized ginger to avoid wasting a couple of dollars. Get the ginger saketini recipe.

Headache-free refreshers
You may make a scrumptious no-buzz drink much like the Kir Royale (which is what this mom-to-be will likely be sipping). Similar to the instructions above, pour the pomegranate juice into the flute, then fill the glass midway with white grape juice and high with glowing water. Or attempt our refreshing and low-cal pomegranate lemonade.

Eats
You don’t have to supply up tons of things at your occasion. A pleasant number of flavorful bites will do.

Garlic shrimp
It is a basic Spanish tapas dish, positive to thrill even Penelope Cruz. Shrimp are solely $7.99/pound or so proper now, they usually’re a low-cal supply of protein. This recipe doesn’t take a lot time, so prepare dinner the shrimp as soon as your visitors arrive. Serve with a facet of greens and a few crusty bread to take in the flavorful juices. Get the garlic shrimp recipe.

Roast garlic and edamame dip
Right here’s one thing that’s Hollywood fabulous: A reasonably light-green dip that places heart-healthy soybeans in a tasty, figure-friendly bundle. And also you don’t need to pay juice bar costs for it. A bag of frozen edamame is barely $three.39. Serve the dip with complete grain crackers, pita chips, sliced jicama, or child carrots. Get the roast garlic and edamame dip recipe.

Particular person chocolate fondues
What’s a black-tie occasion with out one thing wealthy? These seemingly swanky chocolate treats are lower than 150 energy per serving! They’re actually enjoyable for a gaggle and the components received’t price you a fortune. Together with angel meals cake and strawberries, you may also dip bananas (cheaper) or vanilla wafer cookies. Warning—you most likely received’t need to serve these on the sofa. Get the chocolate fondue recipe.

The classics
It’s the flicks, so you could serve some popcorn. However it doesn’t need to be customary concern. A number of individuals are shying away from microwavable baggage of popcorn on account of potential chemical substances which will leach from the bag or the buttery flavorings.

The answer? Make yours the old style method on the range high. Simply put in a layer of kernels, fill the lid with butter (if you want), and pop up this fluffy snack in beneath three minutes.
